---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '~/components/Nav.astro';
import Newsletter from '~/components/Newsletter.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About, Soothemade"
  description="A small studio making slow, considered things for the parts of life no one is photographing."
>
  <Nav />
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <div class="eyebrow">about the studio</div>
      <h1>A small studio, made <em>slowly</em>, in plain language.</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <article class="about">
    <div class="body">
      <p>
        Soothemade is a small studio that makes things, mostly paper
        things, for the long, mostly-unphotographed parts of a life. The
        3 a.m. parts. The Tuesday-with-nothing-planned parts. The
        recovery month. The hour before anyone else is up.
      </p>
      <p>
        What we make is not a system. It is not a productivity hack. It
        is not a routine designed by someone who has never had a quiet
        week. It is a handful of small, considered objects you can use
        through a season and then put down when it is over.
      </p>

      <h2>The rooms in the house</h2>
      <p>
        Soothemade is a master brand. Each line is a different room in
        the same house, same voice, same hands, different season of a
        life. Right now one room is open: <a class="ext" href="https://notes.soothemade.com" rel="noopener">Soothemade Notes</a>, for new parents.
        The other rooms, for the home cook, for the solo worker, for
        the long traveler, are still being made. Slowly. By the same
        people.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can see them on <a href="/lines">the lines page</a>. When a
        new room opens, the easiest way to hear about it is the
        <a href="/newsletter">letter</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we mean by "made slowly"</h2>
      <p>
        We mean the kind of slow that a tomato is. The kind of slow that
        a recovery is. The kind of slow that learning anything actually
        is, before somebody sold you a course that promised otherwise.
        We make one thing at a time. We finish it. We make the next one.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each product is researched, voiced, designed, and read
        end-to-end by a human before it ships. The tools we use to make
        them faster are tools, the way a sewing machine is a tool. They
        do not write your letter and they do not decide what you need.
      </p>

      <h2>What this is not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          A wellness brand. We do not think you have a self to optimize.
          We think you have a life to live, and some of it is plain, and
          we make things for the plain parts.
        </li>
        <li>
          A subscription. You buy a printable, you keep it forever, you
          owe us nothing else.
        </li>
        <li>
          A megaphone. Soothemade is a small thing on purpose. If it
          ever gets larger, the voice you read here is what we are
          accountable to.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where the name comes from</h2>
      <p>
        It is <em>soothe</em> plus <em>-made.</em> It rhymes with
        "homemade" because that is the register. The things in this shop
        are made, slowly, by hand, with the unphotographed days in
        mind.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@soothemade.com">hello@soothemade.com</a>. We read everything. We reply when we can.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
  <Newsletter />
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--container-narrow);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 72px var(--sp-7) 96px;
  }
  .body { font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--apo-paper); }
  .body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 28px;
    margin: 44px 0 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--apo-paper);
  }
  .body p { margin: 0 0 20px; }
  .body em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent-soft); }
  .body ul { margin: 0 0 22px 24px; padding: 0; }
  .body li { margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .body a { color: var(--accent-soft); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--apo-rule-strong); }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .about { padding: 56px var(--sp-5) 72px; }
    .body { font-size: 16px; }
  }
</style>
